[div class=p 
	"TAS of 2007
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"History: After the rewards for each system were given, the winners of those categories were put into a new category for TAs of the year. When everything had finished, we came out with not one, but two winners. 
	(__wikiLink|displaytext=Super Metroid|href=/817M)
	" gained the nod for its commitment to being as entertaining as possible. 
	(__wikiLink|displaytext=Super Mario 64|href=/1017M)
	" won for succeeding at a task that had stumped TASers for quite a while: beating the game without collecting any stars. This was huge news at the time.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Review Super Metroid: This run is a must see, and very worthy of the title for best TAS of 2007. Not only does 
	[a class=intlink href=/Users/Profile/JXQ 
		"JXQ
	]a
	" destroy the game Super Metroid, collecting every item as he does, he does it with style. Highlights include the messages and animation put into the input (he had five controllers running specifically for this purpose) and antics before and after boss fights. 
	$LF
]div
