[div class=p 
	"NES TAS of 2007
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"History: The votes for the NES TAS of the year were very divided. Strong support was given to 
	(__wikiLink|displaytext=Castlevania|href=/901M)
	", 
	(__wikiLink|displaytext=Super Mario Bros 2|href=/1001M)
	", 
	(__wikiLink|displaytext=Journey to Silius|href=/1014M)
	", and 
	(__wikiLink|displaytext=Super Mario Bros|href=/1022M)
	". In the end, Super Mario Bros. was able to win by a sizeable margin. This is because the improvement was so unexpected. It had been over two years since the last Super Mario Bros. movie, and the game had been frame warred to death at that point as well. Many people didn't think improving the run would be possible. 
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Review: 
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"SNES TAS of 2007
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"History: The SNES category had a lot of high profile and highly rated movies, pulling heavily from Mega Man, Metroid, and Mario franchises. Many of these movies were also seriously considered for the star run category when the system was revamped. Two movies in particular got a lot of support, both through votes and on the forums: 
	(__wikiLink|displaytext="All items" Super Metroid|href=/817M)
	", with its humorous input animations and fast paced action; and 
	(__wikiLink|displaytext="small only" Super Mario World|href=/892M)
	", which featured several very creative solutions for getting around the lack of power-ups. Both were entertaining, fast and unique. Super Metroid won the vote in the end and went on to claim the TAS of the year award as well. 
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Sega TAS of 2007
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"History: While many good runs were in this category, two runs dominated the voting. One was 
	(__wikiLink|displaytext=Sonic 3 and Knuckles|href=/826M)
	", which turned the game into a glitchfest on par with Mega Man 2 and warped through levels at lighning speed. The other was 
	(__wikiLink|displaytext=Gunstar Heroes|href=/945M)
	", a long overdue obsoletion which used the versatile game mechanics to make the run as entertaining as possible. Both of these runs went on to receive stars. Other runs, like 
	(__wikiLink|displaytext=Comix Zone|href=/954M)
	" and 
	(__wikiLink|displaytext=Rocket Knight Adventures|href=/958M)
	" only received a few votes, but there were people that showed support for them, usually after declaring they had voted for either Gunstar Heroes or Sonic. 
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Review: Instead of dealing with all the obstacles, Sonic decides to skip everything and go straight to the end.This run hits the perfect balance between glitching and normal gameplay. Nitsuja also makes great use of Tails to save a lot of time and provide some interaction between the two players. This run is fun, fast and surprising.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"GBx TAS of 2007
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"History: The votes for GBx were spread pretty evenly over the different choices. While most people seemed to have a favorite run of the year, there wasn't any large consensus over which one was the best. 
	(__wikiLink|displaytext=Link's Awakening|href=/863M)
	" had a lot of support from people that responded to the topic. The run featured a lot of flashy tricks and was faster paced than most Zelda runs. A later incarnation of that run would receive a star. The silent majority, however, put 
	(__wikiLink|displaytext=Dragonfang's 100% Metroid Zero Mission|href=/981M)
	" on top. The run surprised a lot of people by being incredibly entertaining and impressive throughout its long length. Other runs which gained decent support were 
	(__wikiLink|displaytext=Harmony of Dissonance|href=/995M)
	" and 
	(__wikiLink|displaytext=Aria of Sorrow|href=/1024M)
	".
	$LF
]div
